    "long_instructions": "### Check-In: Dueling Genres\r\n\r\n**Genre** means the style of music like hip-hop, pop, jazz, or rock.\r\n\r\nSanchit wants to create a dueling genres effect in his song.\r\n\r\nHe says:\r\n> I want the beat and bass to sound like one genre for 4 measures, then switch to a different genre for the next 4. Then repeat the whole thing like they're clapping back at each other!\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/2586dbe1a0945ffb9949b4fbcb21714c-image-1745019436109.png)\r\n\r\nTry it out! Listen to the example and build your own.\r\n\r\n**Specific Requirements:**\r\n- Each **beat + bass** combo lasts **4 measures**\r\n- The whole song is **24 measures long**\r\n- Use a **nested loop** to repeat the pattern",
